> and go into receive mode, I am powerless to help :)
>
> At the moment the main difficulty is the difference between the
> 'lossless' 'maximum capture area', for which we have the formula, then
> the smaller 'maximum capture area' when a small antenna is tuned with
> a capacitor (or inductor), then the smallest of all, the 'maximum
> capture area' without tuning.
>
> The theory covers all three, but you must realise from your own branch
> of physics that there is no short-cut to a proper understanding other
> than working through the theory in easy stages - which is why I
> suggested those questions in a previous message.
